P.Span: Select one or more stored processes to filter the graph.

A stored process is a SAS program that is stored on a server and can be executed as required by requesting applications. Your stored processes' source code is categorized by one of two storage types, external or embedded. Source code stored externally exists in external files with a .sas extension on the file system. Embedded source code is stored as part of a SAS object.
This report provides a breakdown of the SAS Stored Processes so you can quickly identify the type and location within your SAS 9 deployment. Common terminology includes:
Deployment.
A deployment is the set of hosts on which the SAS software was deployed.
Embedded storage.
Embedded storage is the source code for the SAS Stored Process which is stored within the object on the SAS Metadata Server.
External file.
An external file is a s
ource code file for the SAS Stored Process which is stored within a file (.sas extension) in the file system.
Project.
A project is a grouping that is derived from the SAS Metadata Server folder path of a SAS Stored Process. For example, Shared Data\ETO Team would be "ETO Team".
The report design may not be updated in each release. The design was last updated in Version 2025.01.
